@baekdal To clarify, I used Netherlands based Blendle, who curated news from multiple sources and allowed for paying per article.  Major Dutch newspapers (Like de Telegraaf) "thought" that Blendle was competing over subscribers and pulled out. Blendle is now a premium service.

@baekdal There are concerns though. Consumers don't necessarily want to pay subscriptions for several papers, just to be able to follow an online debate that quote an article.  Major publications pull out of micro pay initiatives, such as Blendle, who have abandoned micropayments.
